    {
      "text": "Often, people are frustrated if they do not get the right solution for an exercise, whereas \"right\" is defined as the solution the teacher wants to see. This might happen because <i>[[DIFFERENT EXERCISE LEVELS]]</i> are not available. However, the real use of exercises is to have the participants work on them, thereby working on a problem, creatively applying the newly learned topics.\n  ",
      "id": "993a7abdbc2465f4",
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "text": "&lt;center&gt;❖ ❖ ❖&lt;/center&gt;",
